<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I warned ya ;)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?DarkBlight">DarkBlight</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:59 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I warned ya ;)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=770" TARGET=_self>Levels have already killed PvP</A> (Azeraab)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Levels are the meat of EQ. Anyone seriously think 989 is going to a complete turn around and change the entire "base" upon which the game runs on?

<P>*shrugs*
<P>Name of the game is evolve or die, always has been, always will be.
<P>DarkBlight- Facing the crude and cruel facts.
<P>&gt; As many have noticed EQ is totally tied to level to the point
<BR>&gt; where even a group of moderately high level characters cant kill
<BR>&gt; something that is 3 or 4 levels higher than them simply because
<BR>&gt; they will never hit it and it will resist all of their spells.
<BR>&gt; Its the same with PvP, one 20th lvl player will easily wipe out
<BR>&gt; dozens of 10th lvl players. Until this changes I really dont
<BR>&gt; thing EQ will be a viable PvP game.
<P>&gt; At this point I think the tight tie of lvls with xp gains
<BR>&gt; combined with the steep power increases of higher lvl monsters
<BR>&gt; makes EQ a somewhat less than viable PvE game. It certainly
<BR>&gt; keeps it from being very entertaining.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
